
[1]straitness

   STRAITNESS, n.

   1. Narrowness; as the straitness of a place; straitness of mind;
   straitness of circumstances.

   2. Strictness; rigor; as the straitness of a mans proceedings.

   3. Distress; difficulty; pressure from necessity of any kind,
   particularly from poverty.

   4. Want; scarcity; or rather narrowness; as the straitness of the
   conveniences of life.
